The paper focuses on analyzing and detecting information types in open source software issue discussions, which falls under the software engineering (cs.SE) domain. The paper also involves natural language processing techniques such as content analysis and automated classification, which are relevant to information retrieval (cs.IR) and computational linguistics (cs.CL). Additionally, the paper discusses the potential benefits of identifying and obtaining information from issue discussions for various stakeholders, which could be relevant to cybernetics (cs.CY) and social and information networks (cs.SI).
